<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900703-0150</DOCNO><DOCID>900703-0150.</DOCID><HL>   U.S. Tobacco Prices Rise 4.3%</HL><DATE>07/03/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   UST</CO><IN>TOBACCO PRODUCTS (TOB)</IN><LP>   GREENWICH, Conn. -- U.S. Tobacco Sales andamp; Marketing Co.announced a price increase of 4.3% on all its moist smokelesstobacco, effectively immediately.   The subsidiary of U.S. Tobacco Co. raised its prices 7.5%late last year. U.S. Tobacco Sales andamp; Marketing's primarybrands in the smokeless-tobacco market are Copenhagen, Skoal,Skoal Long Cut and Skoal Bandits. The concern also marketspipes, imported cigars and other tobacco-related products.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>